BANGUI, Central African Republic - At least 77 people died in a road accident in the Central African Republic, a hospital official said Wednesday.The accident occurredon Tuesday, about 12km outside Bambari, on the road between Bambari and Ippy in the centre of the country. #Centrafrique: 78 morts dans un accident de la route #Bambari https://t.co/sjF4Xf89Fp pic.twitter.com/5VsJaATX1b Fifty-nine bodies were taken to the hospital morgue in Bambari and 18 others were taken by relatives to be buried, hospital official Michel Zahandji told AFP, while the Medecins Sans Frontieres (MSF) charity said 60 injured people were treated at the hospital.AFP